sentences: Mauro Picotto (born December 25, 1966) is an Italian electronic music producer and DJ, and previously a member of the Italian Euro house group "R.A.F.".
Mauro Picotto (born December 25, 1966) is an Italian electronic music producer and DJ, and previously a member of the Italian Euro house group "R.A.F.".
He now promotes his own club night, Meganite (named after an early 21st-century track of his), which has run for consecutive years annually since 2004 at Privilege Ibiza.

He now produces under his own record label, Bakerloo.
Between 1992 and 1996, R.A.F. would release a number of dance hits, as well as achieving a Top 40 Singles Chart hit in the United Kingdom with "We've Got To Live Together".

Picotto and Bortolotti would see greater success a couple of years later together when another of their co-writes, "Light My Fire", became a big Eurodance hit when remixed by Bortolotti's Cappella, with the song (once licensed to Pete Waterman's PWL Records) becoming a number 7 hit in the United Kingdom in the spring of 1994.

In 1996, Bortolotti decided to make Picotto a partner in Media Records alongside him, while a track released under Picotto's own name, "Bakerloo Symphony", ended up being a number 1 in Italy for eight weeks.1998 saw the release of the Gatecrasher anthem "Lizard (Gonna Get You)".

"I Feel Love" – released under the pseudonym CRW – reached number 15 in 2000, whilst "Communication (Somebody Answer The Phone)" – which he produced alongside Mario Più – reached the UK Top 5 at the end of 1999.

His remix of "On The Beach" by York also helped to propel that song into the UK Top Five in spring 2000, when it was selected by the record company – Manifesto – to be used as the official radio edit.
Two solo albums, The Double Album (2000) and The Others (2002), followed, as well as remixes and productions for Freddie Mercury, Jimmy Somerville, the Pet Shop Boys and U2.

Upon leaving Media Records in 2002, Picotto formed Bakerloo Music, as well as a new label Alchemy, releasing several club tracks, including "New Time New Place" and the "Alchemy EP".
That same year he launched his Meganite party at the Miami Winter Music Conference.

In May 2017 he released another album "A Call In The Club".
On Saturday 7 May 2005, Picotto headlined the dance stage at BBC Radio 1's Big Weekend in Sunderland, in front of thousands of people.
